{"questionId":"9068242","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Aspirin is formed by reacting salicylic acid with ethanoic anhydride. The structure of aspirin is given in section 37 of the data booklet.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6607021398d14bff0315d2a597cad7ef5ec76b82.png\" width=\"404\" height=\"144\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Deduce the structural formula of the by-product of this reaction.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/8ad9c5398a39e7e9ce4eab01aae9125a906a7e58.png\"></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><br><em>Accept full <strong>OR</strong> condensed structural formula.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068242","referenceCode":"20N.3.sl.TZ0.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structural formula of the by-product of this reaction.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}